.th MUL VI "August 1979"
.sh NAME
mul \*- scale a picture by a constant
.sh SYNOPSIS
.bd mul
[constant]
.sh DESCRIPTION
.it Mul
reads a picture's header from the standard input file and echoes
it to the standard output file.
.it Csize
then reads an integer picture of dimension NROW rows by NCOL columns,
where NROW is the number of rows in the input picture and NCOL is
the number of columns in the input  picture,
from the standard input,
multiplies every pixel by
.it constant
and writes it to the standard output file.
.it constant
is 1 if unspecified.
.sh FILES
.sh DIAGNOSTICS
.i0
.lp +35 35
"Header not read"	first 12 bytes of picture not read
.lp +35 35
"Picture width too large"	# of columns in input picture exceeds
input buffer length
.lp +35 35	
"Illegal size"	
.it newsize
< 1 or
.br
.it newsize
> 5
.lp +35 35
"Too much data, row count expired"	# of rows in picture exceeded
.lp +35 35
"Unexpected EOF encountered"	eof encountered before picture completed
.lp +35 35
"Input pipe not empty"	data still resides in input pipe
